    "SBAR, adapted for healthcare by Kaiser Permanente from US Navy nuclear-submarine briefings, structures the call: Situation, Background, Assessment, and Recommendation. The most commonly dropped letter is the R, the explicit ask. Stating findings without a request ('come assess him' or 'may I bolus fluids?') leaves a tired provider guessing and stalls care for an unstable patient.",
